<item>
            <title>[SPARK-32430] Allow plugins to inject rules into AQE query stage preparation</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-32430</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Provide a generic mechanism for plugins to inject rules into the AQE &quot;query prep&quot; stage that happens before query stage creation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this goes along with&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-32332&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-32332&lt;/a&gt;&#160;where the current AQE implementation doesn&apos;t allow for&#160;users to properly extend it for columnar processing.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The issue here is that we create new query stages but we&#160;do not have access to the parent plan of the new query stage so certain things can not be determined because you have to know what the parent did.&#160; With this change it would allow you to add TAGs to be able to figure out what is going on.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
